      "raceComments": "{\"comment\":\"3. MOONLIT POTTER could have just enough to take this small field contest. Second of four when last seen twelve days ago at Huntingdon and subsequently received a small drop in the ratings. Well capable of mixing it from this mark in newly enlisted blinkers. 1. MAXIMUM OFFERS produced a quiet season so far. Arrives fresh from a three-month absence and needs to brush up the jumping a little based on first two efforts. Rates a leading contender against this line-up. 2. JULLOU DE GRISSAY tackles larger obstacles for the first time. Weakened out of contention providing first effort for this yard last month. May strip fitter.\",\"runners\":[3,1,2],\"exclusive\":false}",
